11:
...But not a single person answered
my cries for help.
12: At least, not until I met him.
18:
Hey there, buddy. What's the deal?
Can't even look me in the eyes?
Where are you skittering off to?
20:
I, uh, Nimbus... Um... I just...
I really don't need insurance right
now! I don't have any money!
23:
You idiot! It's exactly people like you
who don't have their act together
that need insurance MOST!
26:
Look here. We're running a
promotion—zero enrollment fees if
you start now. Plus, we'll
recommend you other adventurers
to pair up with. It's a great deal.
You'll love it.
31:
We're well on our way to meeting
our quota, and it's all thanks to
Nimbus! We're one step closer to
ensuring all adventurers in Palpebra
are well looked-after!
33:
Keep up the pace! We're counting
on you!
45:
Ooh. I was worried at first, since your
clothes are so weird and cheerful,
but that mean-looking scowl really
sold me.
47:
You're perfect for the job!
Okay: I hereby give you permission
to kidnap me!
49:
How dare you! I didn't say you could
toss me like that!
52: I'm on the job, kid. Bug off.
54:
Uh-huh... So you're struggling for
money, eh? Then our interests are
perfectly aligned!
56:
Kidnap me! You know, for a ransom!
I'm the son of a very wealthy and
powerful merchant affiliated with
the Guild.
58:
W-wait a minute! Put me down!
LISTEN, damn you! I'm not talking
about a real kidnapping here!
59:
I'm talking about staging it! It'll be a
big ruse!
65:
What do you mean "for what"? Isn't it
obvious? To get back at my dad,
duh!
67:
He's a grade-A scumbag! If you only
knew the terrible things he's done to
people... He's got more enemies
than I can count.
68:
And ever since mom left, the house
has been empty. He never comes
home—he's always "working"...
70:
Scamming people out of their
money, huh? I wonder where you
learned that tactic.
80:
Listen here, Nick. There are plenty
other ways to hit your dad where it
hurts.
82:
If you're set on going through with
this, at least let me teach you a
better way to do it. How's that sound?
88:
Tch... I guess I've gotta get Alk
involved in this mess too.
91:
Hey, mister... You never told me your
name!
96:
Nimbus? Like the cloud? That's
actually kind of cute, haha!
98:
Oy, shut the hell up!
Hey, Alk.
106:
Three days have passed since I last
saw the brat.
111:
Still no leads of any kind. It's hard to
believe that his family hasn't put out
any sort of information about his
disappearance. Isn't that odd?
114:
Very. I suppose the big shots at the
Guild want to keep things on the
down-low? They've got lots to hide,
no doubt.
120:
He's been outside the whole time.
Says he should be able to catch the
boy's scent. His nose is rarely wrong...
126:
I've got bad news for you, kid. Daddy
doesn't seem to want to pay up!
127:
Don't worry, though. You're no use to
us dead. We'll find a way to wring
some money out of you.
129:
What? No waterworks like before?
Heh.
134:
I knew I smelled something rotten
this way.
154:
You know, I consider myself to be
lucky.
157:
Lucky that nobody came for me. I
was all alone too, stranded there in
the desert. I really thought I was
done for.
160:
But you know what? I found a new
home, made new friends—hell, I
even found you in time. I might be
the luckiest damn person that's ever
lived.
162:
And I'm gonna make sure that you
can say the same thing one day.
You can count on that.
167:
And you don't have to. Don't mind
me, I'm just talking to myself.
170:
All right, you remember when I told
you I'd show you how to get back at
your old man? I know just how to do
it.
172:
I'm taking you to this one village
where you can see the stars. It's
filled with the absolute craziest
bunch of people you've ever seen.
They'll teach you what to do.
